    "job_link" : "https://www.quora.com/How-can-a-business-analyst-add-value-to-his-career?-",
    "answer" : "Beyond formal job descriptions, day-to-day responsibilities, acting as an intermediary between different stakeholders, the ultimate job of a BA is to create value for your project/company. And this naturally leads to adding value to the BA’s own career. The key is to play to your strengths as a generalist (breadth), ANDdevelop specialties in one or two areas (depth)This is often referred to as the T-type professional: combining breadth and depth.  Breadth is what you’re already good at — such as working across the organization with a variety of stakeholders, understanding the different technologies used in projects, mastering the client’s business in each project, etc. Depth is one or two areas that you should specialize in — such as enterprise architecting, domain subject matter expertise (e.g. insurance), process expertise (e.g. Kanban), etc.",
    "date" : ISODate("2021-02-24T12:46:08.594Z"),
    "question" : "How can a business analyst add value to his career? ",
