    "job_link" : "https://www.quora.com/Which-CRM-tool-is-better-between-Salesforce-and-MS-Dynamics-for-a-Techno-Functional-Business-analyst-career-growth-prospective?-",
    "answer" : "The answer depends on your target. What company do you have in mind and what system is used there? Some large companies also use Oracle, Netsuite and SAP CRM, so you might also want to consider those other CRM tools. I guess the main considerations in choosing between Dynamics and Salesforce for your career would be these: Your previous experience. It’s easier to build on the knowledge you already have than start from a clean slate. If you’ve got C# and .Net code experience, then it’s easier to transition to MS Dynamics. For Salesforce, you need to be familiar with Apex and Java.The type of organization you want to work for. Dynamics and Salesforce appeal to different kinds of organizations. B2B companies seem to like Salesforce more, while software companies prefer Dynamics.Your preferred deployment. Both Microsoft and Salesforce have CRM in the cloud. Dynamics 365 is a cloud-first product while the SF sales, marketing and service clouds (which comprise the usual CRM system) have always been deployed via the cloud. Microsoft, though, still provides on-premise Dynamics software for companies that prefer legacy systems.If you want to broaden your options and get more opportunities, then maybe you can try learning both the SF CRM and MS Dynamics. Be aware, though, that these two CRM systems are very different from each other. It would take a lot of effort to learn both so be prepared to dedicate a lot of time to such an ambitious project.",
    "date" : ISODate("2021-02-24T13:10:03.361Z"),
    "question" : "Which CRM tool is better between Salesforce and MS Dynamics for a Techno-Functional Business analyst career growth prospective? ",
    "source" : "Quora"
}

